article.headline: Columbia clips Lehigh 54-44
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- Jeff Coby scored 16 points and grabbed 12 rebounds off the bench to lead Columbia over Lehigh 54-44 on Sunday afternoon. Neither team shot the ball well from the field; however the Lions got the free-throw line 18 times and hit six more 3-pointers than did the Mountain Hawks. Cory Osetkowski added with eight points, seven rebounds and five assists for Columbia (1-1), while Maodo Lo finished with nine points and seven boards. Tim Kempton had 15 points and 10 rebounds to lead Lehigh, who finished 0 for 13 from behind the arc. Kahron Ross added 10 points for the Mountain Hawks. Columbia held a 32-23 lead at halftime, helped in large part by a 20-6 scoring stretch midway through the first half.
